  <!-- ============================================================ QUALITY (certs + lab + anatomy) ============================================================ -->
  <main class="view" data-route="/quality" data-title="Quality & Certifications — ISO 9001:2015, ASTM Lab | G Flexipack">
    <section class="sec" style="padding-bottom:40px;">
      <div class="sec-head">
        <p class="pp-crumbs" style="text-align:center;"><a href="#/">Home</a><span>/</span>Quality</p>
        <p class="sec-eyebrow">Quality &amp; certification</p>
        <h2 class="sec-title">Audited, tested, <em>documented.</em></h2>
        <p class="sec-lead">We build every pouch to a specification and prove it in our own lab. Here's how the film is engineered — and how each batch is verified before it ships.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cert-row">
        <div class="cert-emblem"><span class="cert-mark">✦</span><h4>ISO 9001:2015</h4><p>Certified quality management system across procurement, production and dispatch.</p></div>
        <div class="cert-emblem"><span class="cert-mark">✦</span><h4>ASTM Standard QC</h4><p>Eight-test laboratory verification on every batch — GSM to heat-seal strength.</p></div>
        <div class="cert-emblem"><span class="cert-mark">✦</span><h4>100% Recyclable Options</h4><p>Mono-material structures available for EPR-compliant, sustainability-first brands.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lab" id="lab">
      <div class="sec" style="padding-bottom:0;"><div class="sec-head"><p class="sec-eyebrow">The lab</p><h2 class="sec-title">Eight tests. <em>Every batch.</em></h2><p class="sec-lead">Raw material inspected on arrival, colour verified before print, tested in-line at every stage, documented at dispatch.</p></div></div>
      <div class="lab-grid">
        <ol class="test-sheet">
          <li class="test-row"><span class="test-no">01</span><span class="test-name">GSM</span><span class="test-proof">film weight is consistent, roll to roll</span></li>
          <li class="test-row"><span class="test-no">02</span><span class="test-name">COF</span><span class="test-proof">runs smoothly on high-speed filling lines</span></li>
          <li class="test-row"><span class="test-no">03</span><span class="test-name">Bond strength</span><span class="test-proof">laminate layers never separate</span></li>
          <li class="test-row"><span class="test-no">04</span><span class="test-name">Puncture resistance</span><span class="test-proof">survives transit, stacking and handling</span></li>
          <li class="test-row"><span class="test-no">05</span><span class="test-name">Burst strength</span><span class="test-proof">seals hold under internal pressure</span></li>
          <li class="test-row"><span class="test-no">06</span><span class="test-name">Scrub test</span><span class="test-proof">print doesn't rub off in the supply chain</span></li>
          <li class="test-row"><span class="test-no">07</span><span class="test-name">Heat seal strength</span><span class="test-proof">every seam holds, every time</span></li>
          <li class="test-row"><span class="test-no">08</span><span class="test-name">Tear strength</span><span class="test-proof">opens where it should — nowhere else</span></li>
        </ol>
        <div class="lab-side">
          <blockquote class="quality-quote">&ldquo;Quality <em>without</em> compromise.&rdquo;</blockquote>
          <p class="quality-src">Quality policy · tested to ASTM standards</p>
          <div class="lab-photos">
            <figure class="lab-photo" style="margin:0;">{{ img("heat", "Heat seal tester") }}<figcaption>Heat seal tester</figcaption></figure>
            <figure class="lab-photo" style="margin:0;">{{ img("punture", "Puncture and tensile tester") }}<figcaption>Puncture tester</figcaption></figure>
            <figure class="lab-photo" style="margin:0;">{{ img("cutter", "Sample cutter") }}<figcaption>Sample cutter</figcaption></figure>
          </div>
          <div class="cert-line"><span class="cert-chip">ISO 9001:2015</span><span class="cert-chip">ASTM Standard QC</span><span class="cert-chip">100% Recyclable Options</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="anatomy" id="anatomy">
      <div class="sec-head"><p class="sec-eyebrow">Inside the film</p><h2 class="sec-title">A pouch is <em>three decisions,</em> laminated together.</h2><p class="sec-lead">What keeps chips crisp for nine months isn't the print — it's the structure behind it. Scroll through the layers we bond for every job.</p></div>
      <div class="anatomy-grid">
        <div class="anatomy-sticky"><div class="film-stack" id="filmStack" data-step="1" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="sheet sheet-print"><span class="sheet-label">Print · BOPP / PET</span></div>
          <div class="sheet sheet-barrier"><span class="sheet-label">Barrier · MET-PET / AL</span></div>
          <div class="sheet sheet-seal"><span class="sheet-label">Seal · LLDPE / CPP</span></div>
          <p class="stack-caption">One film. <em>Your structure.</em></p>
        </div></div>
        <div class="anatomy-steps">
          <div class="a-step" data-step="1"><p class="a-step-num">01</p><h3>The print carrier</h3><p>Your artwork is reverse-printed in up to eight colours on rotogravure — so the ink sits <b>inside</b> the laminate. It can't scuff, scratch or fade on shelf, no matter how rough the supply chain is.</p></div>
          <div class="a-step" data-step="2"><p class="a-step-num">02</p><h3>The barrier core</h3><p>Metallised PET or aluminium foil blocks oxygen, moisture and light. This layer is why roasted, fried and dried products stay fresh for months — and it's specified per product, not per catalogue.</p></div>
          <div class="a-step" data-step="3"><p class="a-step-num">03</p><h3>The food-contact seal</h3><p>LLDPE or CPP on the inside — food-grade, heat-sealable, and strong enough to run on high-speed filling lines without splitting a single seam.</p></div>
          <div class="a-step" data-step="4"><p class="a-step-num">04</p><h3>Bonded into one film</h3><p>Solvent-less lamination fuses the layers into a single web — then it's slit, pouched and batch-tested in our own QC lab before dispatch. Common structures we run:</p>
            <div class="laminate-chips"><span class="laminate-chip">BOPP / MET-PET / PE</span><span class="laminate-chip">PET / AL / LLDPE</span><span class="laminate-chip is-reel">Mono LLDPE — recyclable</span><span class="laminate-chip">CPP / AL / PET</span><span class="laminate-chip">PET / PE</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="pp-band"><div class="sec"><h2>Packaging you can <em>document and defend.</em></h2><p>Every order ships with test documentation. Send your brief for a structure recommendation within {{ site.quoteTurnaround }}.</p><a class="cta cta-light" href="#/inquiry">Get a quote <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></div></section>
